===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} of a long river with [[tributary|tributaries]]. Cognate with {{zh-l|*𠂢}}, {{zh-l|*派}}. 

Alternatively, {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} of a person swimming in the water. Original form of {{och-l|泳}}.

===Etymology===
{{unc|zh}}.
* STEDT compares {{och-l|永}} to provisional {{cog|tbq-lob-pro|-}} meso-root {{m|tbq-lob-pro|*ʔ-m(y)aŋ¹/³}};
* {{zh-ref|Bodman (1980)}} derived {{och-l|永}} from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*wrjaŋ}} & considered it cognate with {{cog|lep|ᰝᰥᰤᰰ|tr=hryăn}} as well as {{cog|bo|རྒྱོང་བ||to extend; to stretch}} and {{m|bo|རྒྱང་མ||distance}};
* {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} considered to be unclear any connection with {{och-l|泂}} and {{cog|bo|རིང||to be tall, long}}, {{cog|tdg|rehng pā||to be long}}, {{cog|my|ရှည်||to be long}}, (all from {{cog|sit-pro|*s-r(i/u)ŋ||to be long, to elongate}}) & {{cog|tbq-lol-pro|*s/m-riŋ||long (adv.)}}; so Schuessler compared {{och-l|永}} to {{cog|km|វែង||long}} and {{cog|km|បង្វែង||to prolong, divert, mislead, deceive}} (both from {{cog|mkh-pro|*waiŋ||long}}).

